<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-229] Document how to disable Lustre console message rate limiting</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-229</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It would be helpful to draw attention to the libcfs module parameter which disables Lustre console message rate limiting.  This module parameter is called libcfs_console_ratelimit.  Here is its documentation from &quot;modinfo libcfs&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;parm:           libcfs_console_ratelimit:Lustre kernel debug console ratelimit (0 to disable) (uint)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A short section could be added under section 29.2 &quot;Lustre Debugging Procedures&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
